---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Humanoids — Formic"
  description="Humanoid and bimanual mobile platforms deployed under Formic Full Service. Frontier general-purpose robotics for mid-market manufacturing — fixed monthly price, no CapEx."
  ogTitle="Humanoids — Formic"
  ogDescription="Generalist robots, as a service. Humanoid platforms under the Formic Full Service model."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/solutions/humanoids" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/solutions">Solutions</a><span class="sep">/</span>Humanoids
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Humanoids</div>
    <h1>Generalist robots,<br><em>as a service.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Humanoid and bimanual mobile platforms — frontier general-purpose hardware deployed, supported, and continuously upgraded under Formic Full Service. You get the upside; we carry the integration risk.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Humanoid-factory.jpg">
        <source src="/ATLAS_EOAT.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-cap">Bimanual platform · pilot cell</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Why Now</div>
      <h2>General-purpose robotics is <em>finally shipping</em>.</h2>
      <p>For decades, general-task automation was the perpetual "five years away" of manufacturing. That changed — bimanual mobile platforms are running production cycles in pilots today, and humanoids are entering early customer trials. Formic is the deployment partner for mid-market manufacturers who want frontier capability without standing up a robotics R&amp;D shop.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Pilots designed and run by Formic engineers</li>
        <li>Same Full Service model — fixed monthly price, no CapEx, all support included</li>
        <li>Continuous OTA upgrades as capability matures</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Humanoid-factory.jpg" alt="Humanoid robot working on a factory floor" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Frontier · production trial</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Talos-9787.jpg">
        <source src="/ATLAS_EOAT.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <span class="img-cap">Mobile · bimanual</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Pilots</div>
      <h2>Pilot today. <em>Scale tomorrow.</em></h2>
      <p>Bimanual mobile robots already handle multi-step manipulation — bin picking, machine tending, assist work — and relocate between cells without a fixed footprint. We're running humanoid pilots with select customers in 2026 and 2027, scoped narrowly to one task and one cell, and expanded only when the platform proves out the economics.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Vendor-neutral — we run the best platform for your task</li>
        <li>Scoped to your highest-friction tasks, one cell at a time</li>
        <li>OTA capability rollouts without hardware swaps</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/talk-with-an-expert" class="larr">Discuss a pilot →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Frontier capability,<br><em>without the R&amp;D shop.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="/talk-with-an-expert" class="btn-ctadark">Talk with an Expert</a>
    <a href="/solutions" class="btn-ctawh">All Solutions</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
